<br>
Monks<br>
Sks<br>
Enchanters<br>
<br>
you might ask why I have enchanters on my list well I have to say them slowing a mob then mezzing it is one of the better pulling tactics I have seen.<br>
<br>
Some say SKs cant instant FD so they suck. I am sorry that is not true. When you are pulling, you are bring mobs back to a group, or close enough to a group before you FD. You have plenty of time to get off a FD before the mob even hits you. Also even when you get hit you can still get FD off. The other benefit SKs have over monks is what I like to call Agro pulling. (i.e Shadowy Assassin in UP if you IVU  u can agro him solo and bring him to camp Solo, or Ancient Totem in PoG you can invis and solo pull him with 4 mobs around by letting him agro you) Since SKs can self invis and IVU they have the advantage is certain situations over monks.<br>
<br>
Monks What more can I say.<br>
<br>
I honestly think it isnt the class that makes a great puller it is the player. So players just understand and enjoy the puller role no matter if they are an SK, Monk, Bard, etc... It is all about pulling tactics!<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
